{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GMhJe79suS2k2Rjoa6fbzk","type":"tool_result","content":"  1500→\n  1501→  // Remove pre-merged continuation prefix singles: buildCandidates now emits both the original\n  1502→  // standalone line AND the pre-merged continuation form (both single origin). The standalone\n  1503→  // prefix must be suppressed when the longer merged form also survived the threshold.\n  1504→  // Example: \"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce\" (standalone) gets removed when\n  1505→  //          \"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander\" (pre-merged) is present.\n  1506→  const survivingMergedSingles = selected.filter((s) => {\n  1507→    if (s.origin !== \"single\") return false;\n  1508→    const t = s.text.toLowerCase();\n  1509→    return selected.some((other) => {\n  1510→      if (other === s || other.origin !== \"single\") return false;\n  1511→      const o = other.text.toLowerCase();\n  1512→      if (!o.startsWith(t + \" \")) return false;\n  1513→      const remainder = o.slice(t.length + 1);\n  1514→      return /^[/&+:(]/.test(remainder);\n  1515→    });\n  1516→  });\n  1517→  if (survivingMergedSingles.length > 0) {\n  1518→    const mergedSingleTexts = new Set(survivingMergedSingles.map((s) => s.text.toLowerCase()));\n  1519→    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n  1520→      if (s.origin !== \"single\") return true;\n  1521→      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n  1522→      return !survivingMergedSingles.some((m) => {\n  1523→        const mLower = m.text.toLowerCase();\n  1524→        if (!mLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \")) return false;\n  1525→        const remainder = mLower.slice(sLower.length + 1);\n  1526→        return /^[/&+:(]/.test(remainder);\n  1527→      });\n  1528→    });\n  1529→  }\n  1530→\n  1531→  // Pre-dedup: remove sub-section headers that are substrings of other surviving candidates.\n  1532→  // A sub-section header is an ALL_CAPS candidate followed by ingredient-like lines in the source.\n  1533→  // Example: \"CHLEBEK\" (bread section header, followed by \"500 g mąki\") is a substring of\n  1534→  // \"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\" (the real title). Without this filter, dedup kills the title.\n  1535→  selected = selected.filter((candidate) => {\n  1536→    if (!isAllCaps(candidate.text)) return true;\n  1537→    // Check if this candidate is immediately followed by ingredient-like content\n  1538→    const nextSourceLines = lines.slice(candidate.position + 1, candidate.position + 2);\n  1539→    const followedByIngredients = nextSourceLines.some(\n  1540→      (l) => looksLikeIngredient(l.trim()) || startsWithNumber(l.trim())\n  1541→    );\n  1542→    if (!followedByIngredients) return true;\n  1543→    // Only remove if a longer candidate contains this one as a substring\n  1544→    const candidateLower = candidate.text.toLowerCase();\n  1545→    const hasLongerParent = rawScored.some(\n  1546→      (other) =>\n  1547→        other.text !== candidate.text &&\n  1548→        other.text.length > candidate.text.length &&\n  1549→        other.text.toLowerCase().includes(candidateLower)\n  1550→    );\n  1551→    return !hasLongerParent;\n  1552→  });\n  1553→\n  1554→  // Protect multi-line joins from being destroyed by their own component singles.\n  1555→  // When \"Lamb Stew\" (2-line join) survives AND both \"Lamb\" and \"Stew\" (singles) also survive,\n  1556→  // the join is the intended title — remove the singles.\n  1557→  const joinsToProtect = selected.filter((s) => s.origin === \"2-line\" || s.origin === \"3-line\");\n  1558→  if (joinsToProtect.length > 0) {\n  1559→    const singlesToRemove = new Set<string>();\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04298fa1-86d9-4110-91db-17d42e86a59f","uuid":"8d3f8ce2-8bb4-47e0-ae66-43b3b9dee04e","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts","content":"\n  // Remove pre-merged continuation prefix singles: buildCandidates now emits both the original\n  // standalone line AND the pre-merged continuation form (both single origin). The standalone\n  // prefix must be suppressed when the longer merged form also survived the threshold.\n  // Example: \"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce\" (standalone) gets removed when\n  //          \"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander\" (pre-merged) is present.\n  const survivingMergedSingles = selected.filter((s) => {\n    if (s.origin !== \"single\") return false;\n    const t = s.text.toLowerCase();\n    return selected.some((other) => {\n      if (other === s || other.origin !== \"single\") return false;\n      const o = other.text.toLowerCase();\n      if (!o.startsWith(t + \" \")) return false;\n      const remainder = o.slice(t.length + 1);\n      return /^[/&+:(]/.test(remainder);\n    });\n  });\n  if (survivingMergedSingles.length > 0) {\n    const mergedSingleTexts = new Set(survivingMergedSingles.map((s) => s.text.toLowerCase()));\n    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n      if (s.origin !== \"single\") return true;\n      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n      return !survivingMergedSingles.some((m) => {\n        const mLower = m.text.toLowerCase();\n        if (!mLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \")) return false;\n        const remainder = mLower.slice(sLower.length + 1);\n        return /^[/&+:(]/.test(remainder);\n      });\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Pre-dedup: remove sub-section headers that are substrings of other surviving candidates.\n  // A sub-section header is an ALL_CAPS candidate followed by ingredient-like lines in the source.\n  // Example: \"CHLEBEK\" (bread section header, followed by \"500 g mąki\") is a substring of\n  // \"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\" (the real title). Without this filter, dedup kills the title.\n  selected = selected.filter((candidate) => {\n    if (!isAllCaps(candidate.text)) return true;\n    // Check if this candidate is immediately followed by ingredient-like content\n    const nextSourceLines = lines.slice(candidate.position + 1, candidate.position + 2);\n    const followedByIngredients = nextSourceLines.some(\n      (l) => looksLikeIngredient(l.trim()) || startsWithNumber(l.trim())\n    );\n    if (!followedByIngredients) return true;\n    // Only remove if a longer candidate contains this one as a substring\n    const candidateLower = candidate.text.toLowerCase();\n    const hasLongerParent = rawScored.some(\n      (other) =>\n        other.text !== candidate.text &&\n        other.text.length > candidate.text.length &&\n        other.text.toLowerCase().includes(candidateLower)\n    );\n    return !hasLongerParent;\n  });\n\n  // Protect multi-line joins from being destroyed by their own component singles.\n  // When \"Lamb Stew\" (2-line join) survives AND both \"Lamb\" and \"Stew\" (singles) also survive,\n  // the join is the intended title — remove the singles.\n  const joinsToProtect = selected.filter((s) => s.origin === \"2-line\" || s.origin === \"3-line\");\n  if (joinsToProtect.length > 0) {\n    const singlesToRemove = new Set<string>();","numLines":60,"startLine":1500,"totalLines":1753}}}
